          "body": "## Summary\n\n`/workspaces/ocr-container/scripts/style-review-detect.py` runs `claude -p --bare` as a subprocess to perform LLM-based convention detection. When that subprocess fails (returncode != 0) — e.g. no tty / no auth available in a background-subagent context — the script silently falls through to `_parse_response(\"\")`, which returns `{\"findings\": []}`. Callers can't distinguish 'detection ran cleanly and found nothing' from 'detection didn't run at all.'\n\n## Repro\n\nRun `uv run python scripts/style-review-detect.py --pr <N> --repo <repo>` from a context where `claude -p` lacks auth (e.g. a backgrounded Agent subagent). Script returns an empty findings JSON; no error surfaced.\n\n## Surfaced by\n\nR4 closeout: PR #17 review agent (`afec1b702bccfb635`) ran style-review-detect.py from a background subagent context. The subprocess returned exit 1; the script returned `{\"findings\": []}`; all 11 actual findings had to be produced by manual diff analysis instead.\n\n## Suggested fix\n\nIn `_call_claude` (or wherever the subprocess is invoked), check `result.returncode != 0`; raise / propagate an exception or write a clear stderr message + non-zero script exit, so callers know detection didn't run.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- [ ] Subprocess failure produces a non-zero exit + diagnostic stderr (not a silent empty-findings JSON).\n- [ ] Regression test covers the failure path with a mocked subprocess returning exit 1.\n- [ ] Existing happy-path tests still pass.\n\n## Originally filed on\n\nConcaveTrillion/pd-book-tools#43 — closed there (wrong repo for workspace-tooling bugs).",
